#1. Inputs are taken of height in meters and weight in kilogram
height = input("enter your height in m: ")
weight = input("enter your weight in kg: ")
#2. Converted to floating datatype
h = float(height)
w = float(weight)
#3. Actual formula is applied to get bmi of a person
bmi = w // (h**2)
#4. Print the bmi in floating datatype
print(f"Your BMI is {bmi}")

